  "text": "The Envoy xDS v2 to v3 API migration is implemented across multiple C++ source files that handle both SotW (State-of-the-World) and Delta xDS protocols. Key findings:\n\n**Type URL to Service Mapping (source/common/config/type_to_endpoint.cc):** This file implements the critical conversion from resource type URLs (e.g., 'type.googleapis.com/envoy.config.route.v3.RouteConfiguration') to v3 gRPC service methods. The typeUrlToV3ServiceMap() function explicitly enumerates all v3 service discovery services including RouteDiscoveryService, ClusterDiscoveryService, EndpointDiscoveryService, ListenerDiscoveryService, RuntimeDiscoveryService, SecretDiscoveryService, ScopedRoutesDiscoveryService, VirtualHostDiscoveryService, LocalityEndpointDiscoveryService, and ExtensionConfigDiscoveryService. Functions deltaGrpcMethod() and sotwGrpcMethod() map resource types to their respective gRPC endpoints.\n\n**ADS gRPC Server and Mux Implementation:** The xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.cc implements both GrpcMuxSotw and GrpcMuxDelta classes that inherit from GrpcMuxImpl. These are templated classes parameterized by subscription state type and request/response message types (either envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest/DiscoveryResponse for SotW or envoy::service::discovery::v3::DeltaDiscoveryRequest/DeltaDiscoveryResponse for Delta). The dual-version subscription handling multiplexes multiple resource subscriptions on a single gRPC stream.\n\n**Subscription State Management:** The sotw_subscription_state.cc implements SotwSubscriptionState which inherits from BaseSubscriptionState<envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryResponse, envoy::service::discovery::v3::DiscoveryRequest>. The handleGoodResponse() function processes v3 DiscoveryResponse messages. Similarly, delta_subscription_state.h/.cc in the xds_mux directory implements DeltaSubscriptionState for delta protocol handling with v3 DeltaDiscoveryResponse/DeltaDiscoveryRequest types. The addResourceStateFromServer() function processes v3 Resource messages from delta responses.\n\n**v2 to v3 Versioning:** The utility.h file contains checkTransportVersion() which validates and enforces v3-only transport (V2 is deprecated). The api_version.h defines ApiVersion enum with V2 (deprecated, value 1) and V3 (value 2). Proto annotations in api/envoy/service/discovery/v3/discovery.proto show versioning migration with (udpa.annotations.versioning).previous_message_type pointing to v2 equivalents (e.g., 'envoy.api.v2.DiscoveryRequest').\n\n**Proto Field Mappings:** The v3 discovery.proto defines DiscoveryRequest with version_info field (from v2), and updated field names in v3 like resource_names_subscribe in DeltaDiscoveryRequest. Both SotW and Delta message types are fully v3 with no inline v2 handling - the v2 to v3 conversion happens at the proto compilation stage and configuration validation layer.\n\n**Configuration Subscription Factory:** The grpc_subscription_impl.cc creates GrpcSubscriptionImpl instances that use the GrpcMux (either legacy or unified). The factory pattern in grpc_subscription_factory.cc creates either SotwGrpcMuxFactory or DeltaGrpcMuxFactory based on transport_api_version and api_type configuration, delegating actual mux implementation selection to the unified GrpcMuxSotw or GrpcMuxDelta classes in xds_mux/grpc_mux_impl.cc.\n\nThis architecture cleanly separates v3 protocol handling (on the wire) from internal subscription state management, with type_to_endpoint.cc serving as the central mapping point for resource type discovery across all xDS APIs."
}

